{
    "scenesflat": [
        {
            "timeflat": 1000,
            "typeflat": "book",
            "contentflat": [
                "Gates"
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 100,
            "typeflat": "p",
            "contentflat": [
                ""
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 2550,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "Gates: Strings create everything,",
                "including space and time and even us."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 4800,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "The way",
                "that this is done is unfortunately extremely mathematical and detailed,",
                "but I can use an analogy."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 3300,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "If I took a little piece of spaghetti and plucked it,",
                "it would vibrate back and forth."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 1200,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "As it vibrates, it makes a note."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 1800,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "The note that you get depends on how you pluck it."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 4500,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "Roughly speaking, the idea of strings is that",
                "when you pluck it a certain way you might be looking",
                "at an electron."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 2700,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "When you pluck it a different way you might see a particle",
                "of light."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 2250,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "If you pluck it a third way you might be looking",
                "at a quark."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 3300,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "All the particles are in fact different vibratory modes",
                "of this single object."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 100,
            "typeflat": "p",
            "contentflat": [
                ""
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 2100,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "NOVA: Why are physicists so excited about strings?"
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 2250,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "How do they advance our understanding",
                "of the universe?"
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 100,
            "typeflat": "p",
            "contentflat": [
                ""
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 3450,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "Gates: For about 2,000 years essentially all",
                "of our physics has been based on billiard balls."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 8100,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "The technical name is geometrical point particle,",
                "but the idea at the end of the day was that",
                "if you can figure out how billiard balls work,",
                "then you can actually figure out everything."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 4800,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "It got us to the moon, it got us computers,",
                "it got us all sorts of marvelous technologies",
                "that we now take for granted."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 4650,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "But these billiard balls also ran us",
                "into a conflict",
                "between general relativity and quantum mechanics."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 1650,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "String theory seems to get us out of this."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 10350,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "I think Einstein would be extremely happy",
                "with the way things developed, because he called",
                "for a unified field theory long",
                "before anyone else imagined that such a thing was possible,",
                "and string theory very definitely is a unified field theory."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 100,
            "typeflat": "p",
            "contentflat": [
                ""
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 1200,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "NOVA: Backtrack for us a bit."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 1950,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "What do you mean by a unified field theory?"
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 100,
            "typeflat": "p",
            "contentflat": [
                ""
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 2100,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "Gates: We have observed four forces",
                "in action in nature."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 1200,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "There's the force of gravity."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 4950,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "There's the electromagnetic force&mdash;we use",
                "that in computers, we use that",
                "in our modern information technology."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 2850,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "There is the strong nuclear force, the force",
                "from which the sun derives its energy."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 5100,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "We found the weak nuclear force when substances",
                "that were naturally radioactive, such",
                "as radium, were found to glow in the dark."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 1000,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "Could there be more forces?"
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 1000,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "The answer is yes."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 5700,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "There could be more, but we have not seen them",
                "in laboratory experiments, and physics is always",
                "about what we see in the laboratory."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 3150,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "A unified field theory has to explain",
                "all of this and include gravity."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 100,
            "typeflat": "p",
            "contentflat": [
                ""
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 3000,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "<br />&ldquo;Gravity is the odd man out",
                "for deep philosophical reasons.&rdquo;"
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 100,
            "typeflat": "p",
            "contentflat": [
                ""
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 1000,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "&nbsp;"
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 100,
            "typeflat": "p",
            "contentflat": [
                ""
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 6750,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "In the 1930s some physicists tried",
                "to study Einstein's equations",
                "of gravitation and combine those with the new laws",
                "of quantum theory, the physics of very small objects."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 3750,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "When you try to put those two pieces",
                "of mathematics together, they do not coexist peacefully."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 2100,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "In fact, you get nonsense",
                "out of those calculations."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 5250,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "And so until string theory came",
                "along there was this schism in which we had some laws",
                "that we knew worked very well but only for small things."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 2850,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "We had other laws that worked very well",
                "for large things in gravitation."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 1800,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "But when you tried",
                "to combine the laws, they broke down."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 5700,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "It was only with string theory that we found a way",
                "to successfully marry these two very different sets",
                "of mathematical equations."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 100,
            "typeflat": "p",
            "contentflat": [
                ""
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 4200,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "<br />The fourth force <br />NOVA:",
                "Why has gravity resisted being incorporated",
                "with the other forces?"
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 100,
            "typeflat": "p",
            "contentflat": [
                ""
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 2700,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "Gates: Gravity is the odd man out",
                "for deep philosophical reasons."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 5700,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "When Newton wrote down his mathematical description",
                "of gravity, there was an assumption lurking",
                "in the equations; they didn't depend on time."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 5550,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "His equations say that something",
                "in one location can have an effect",
                "at another location far removed at the instant that it occurs."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 4800,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "So the instant something happens here,",
                "it's automatically and instantaneously known",
                "at the second location."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 6150,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "This idea of action at distance,",
                "which is an almost magical kind of idea,",
                "sits conceptually under Newton's description of gravity."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 5700,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "Newton was aware of this and in his famous Principia spoke",
                "about the philosophical unpleasantness",
                "of including such an idea."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 100,
            "typeflat": "p",
            "contentflat": [
                ""
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 4650,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "As soon as Einstein wrote down his equations,",
                "we understood that action",
                "at a distance cannot apply in our universe."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 9900,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "Einstein's equations say that when an event occurs",
                "in one location, it takes some amount of time",
                "before it is known in another location;",
                "the fastest that the communication",
                "between these two separated points can occur is at the speed of light."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 6300,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "The notion that there's a time separation",
                "between cause and effect leads us",
                "to the notion",
                "that something actually carries the information back and forth."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 4800,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "For the electromagnetic forces and",
                "by extension all the other forces,",
                "those carriers are things like the photon."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 8700,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "When you look at Einstein's equations,",
                "since they are so very radically different",
                "from Maxwell's equations, the object",
                "that carries the information",
                "about the disturbance is something drastically different."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 1500,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "This carrier is called the graviton."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 7200,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "Part of the reason the descriptions",
                "could not be coalesced is that the equations",
                "of gravity are just so radically different",
                "from the equations of all the other forces."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 100,
            "typeflat": "p",
            "contentflat": [
                ""
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 1800,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "NOVA: What is the nature of those gravitons?"
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 100,
            "typeflat": "p",
            "contentflat": [
                ""
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 2250,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "Gates:",
                "Einstein's equations describe how space and time are curved."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 7950,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "The analogy is that the universe is like a sheet",
                "of rubber, and when you put a piece of mass some place,",
                "it dents the rubber and causes things to fall in,",
                "and that's analogous to how gravity works."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 5100,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "Now, if you were to take that mass that you dropped",
                "on a sheet of rubber and jiggle it back and forth,",
                "what would happen to the sheet of rubber?"
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 4350,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "Very quickly you would build",
                "up ripples on the sheet of rubber",
                "as you take the mass point and jiggle it back and forth."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 1500,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "Those ripples are in fact the graviton."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 5550,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "So it's the waves of gravitational energy",
                "in spacetime that are responsible",
                "for communicating the gravitational force."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 100,
            "typeflat": "p",
            "contentflat": [
                ""
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 3900,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "<br />Inside Einstein's mind <br />NOVA:",
                "It's become a clich&eacute; that Einstein was a genius."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 3000,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "What was it about the way he approached problems",
                "that made him such a genius?"
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 100,
            "typeflat": "p",
            "contentflat": [
                ""
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 3300,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "Gates: Einstein made the statement once",
                "that imagination is more important than knowledge."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 2100,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "For a long time I was very puzzled",
                "by this statement."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 7200,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "How could it be that imagination&mdash;which I associated",
                "with play fantasies and hobbits and such matters&mdash;how",
                "could it possibly be that",
                "that was more important than knowledge?"
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 6900,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "Now, having worked as a physicist for",
                "over two decades, I think he was saying that",
                "when you try to create new knowledge, the",
                "only tool we have as humans is our imagination."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 3150,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "The creation",
                "of new rational paradigms is itself an irrational process."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 100,
            "typeflat": "p",
            "contentflat": [
                ""
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 7950,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "The genius of Einstein was such that when he wrote",
                "down his marvelously complicated equations",
                "of general relativity, he gave a picture for",
                "what the equations meant, and why they had to be."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 3900,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "Suppose you were in an elevator standing on the surface",
                "of the Earth and had a ball in your hand."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 1350,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "You let go of the ball and it falls."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 3150,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "You wouldn't think very much about that",
                "because that's how gravity always acts."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 6150,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "But suppose that I take you in this elevator with no windows",
                "so you can't see out, and I put a rocket motor",
                "under it and I put you out in space."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 4500,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "Then I turn the rocket motor on so",
                "that it causes the acceleration to occur within the elevator."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 5400,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "You're moving faster and faster, and you're standing",
                "on the floor of the elevator and you have this same ball",
                "in your hand, and you let go."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 100,
            "typeflat": "p",
            "contentflat": [
                ""
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 3600,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "<br />&ldquo;Einstein was one of those physicists",
                "who really wanted to know the mind of God.&rdquo;"
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 100,
            "typeflat": "p",
            "contentflat": [
                ""
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 1000,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "&nbsp;"
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 100,
            "typeflat": "p",
            "contentflat": [
                ""
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 1000,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "What happens to the ball?"
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 1950,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "It appears from your point",
                "of view to fall to the floor."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 9450,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "So for this man in the elevator,",
                "he cannot tell whether he is standing on the surface",
                "of the Earth, a gravitating body, or whether he is out",
                "in free space with a rocket that's driving the elevator",
                "to greater and greater speeds."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 5400,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "When you translate that story to mathematics,",
                "it turns out you get Einstein's equations,",
                "and that's what we're missing for string theory."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 2100,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "We're still looking for that man in the elevator."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 3000,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "[For more on Einstein and his genius,",
                "see the NOVA Web site Einstein Revealed.]"
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 100,
            "typeflat": "p",
            "contentflat": [
                ""
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 1950,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "NOVA: How was this theory received at the time?"
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 2550,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "Did people accept it,",
                "or was it too radical an idea?"
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 100,
            "typeflat": "p",
            "contentflat": [
                ""
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 3900,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "Gates: A prediction of this bending and flexing",
                "of the spacetime grid is",
                "that light from stars can be bent."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 7650,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "At the end of the First World War an expedition returned",
                "from South America and said we've seen the bending",
                "of starlight precisely as the theory",
                "of general relativity predicts."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 2100,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "At that point the second great crowning",
                "of Einstein occurred."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 1650,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "He was already a world-famous scientist."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 1800,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "This one broke out into popular media."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 1500,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "Einstein was like a rock star in his day."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 100,
            "typeflat": "p",
            "contentflat": [
                ""
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 2700,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "NOVA: Why did Einstein pursue the idea",
                "of unification?"
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 100,
            "typeflat": "p",
            "contentflat": [
                ""
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 3150,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "Gates: Einstein clearly had a large spiritual dimension",
                "to his thinking."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 5100,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "He talked about God, and he clearly believed",
                "that the universe has an overall grand and beautiful pattern",
                "to the way it works."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 4050,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "With his achievement of special relativity, more",
                "of that apparent pattern was revealed to mankind."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 2400,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "But he also understood that it",
                "could not be the full pattern."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 4950,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "Einstein was one of those physicists",
                "who really wanted to know the mind of God,",
                "which more prosaically means the entire picture."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 100,
            "typeflat": "p",
            "contentflat": [
                ""
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 1500,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "NOVA: But he failed in that endeavor?"
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 100,
            "typeflat": "p",
            "contentflat": [
                ""
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 4950,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "Gates: By the time of Einstein's death",
                "in the '50s almost no serious physicists were engaged",
                "in the quest for unification."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 5100,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "He was thought to be this doddering,",
                "sympathetic old figure",
                "who led an earlier revolution but somehow fell out of it."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 2250,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "There's a sadness",
                "about the latter part of his career."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 5700,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "But now, 50 years after his death, it looks quite different,",
                "because we can see unification coming back",
                "in a major way and having profound impacts."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 10200,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "The idea of unification is such a potent one",
                "that even though the scientific community apparently dropped it,",
                "the structure of the universe seems",
                "to demand it, and the community is driven back",
                "to the idea of unification."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 100,
            "typeflat": "p",
            "contentflat": [
                ""
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 3600,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "<br />Seeking unification <br />NOVA: Why",
                "should unification matter to most people?"
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 2550,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "Does it have any practical applications",
                "in the real world?"
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 100,
            "typeflat": "p",
            "contentflat": [
                ""
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 8400,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "Gates: Unification has driven science",
                "for about 150 years,",
                "and every time we've used the idea it has brought us a broader and deeper understanding",
                "of science, which ultimately advances our technology."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 4650,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "The unification",
                "of magnets and electricity was carried out",
                "by a British scientist named James Clerk Maxwell in 1864."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 4050,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "He wrote four equations that are the code",
                "for modern developments such",
                "as computers, cell phones, and beepers."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 2850,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "In this sense physics provides us",
                "with the DNA for advanced technology."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 100,
            "typeflat": "p",
            "contentflat": [
                ""
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 2550,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "NOVA: Is the elegance of",
                "that something that appeals to you?"
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 100,
            "typeflat": "p",
            "contentflat": [
                ""
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 3750,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "Gates: The drive for unity is certainly",
                "to me one of the deepest elegances of physics."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 3750,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "It's a tradition that we've been following",
                "as a community since the work of Newton."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 5700,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "One way to view Newton's explanation of gravity",
                "with the famous story of the dropping apple is",
                "that he unified the heavens with Earth."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 6450,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "He said that something that happens here",
                "on Earth&mdash;namely an apple dropping",
                "off a tree&mdash;is directly connected",
                "with the paths of objects we see in the heavens."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 2700,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "That's a kind of reconnection of,",
                "in some sense, Earth and heaven."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 4050,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "We've been doing this for a long time,",
                "so my own personal feeling is",
                "that there's a rightness about this."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 100,
            "typeflat": "p",
            "contentflat": [
                ""
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 5550,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "NOVA: How do you respond to critics of string theory",
                "who say it can't be proved experimentally,",
                "so it's not really science?"
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 100,
            "typeflat": "p",
            "contentflat": [
                ""
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 7200,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "Gates: String theory is often criticized",
                "as having had no experimental input or output,",
                "so the analogy to a religion has been noted",
                "by a number of people."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 2700,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "In a sense that's right; it is kind",
                "of a church to which I belong."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 1650,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "We have our own popes and House of Cardinals."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 5700,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "But ultimately science is also an act",
                "of faith&mdash;faith that we will be capable",
                "of understanding the way the universe is put together."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 100,
            "typeflat": "p",
            "contentflat": [
                ""
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 3000,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "NOVA: But what are the reasons for believing",
                "that string theory is correct?"
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 100,
            "typeflat": "p",
            "contentflat": [
                ""
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 6300,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "Gates:",
                "The well-known physicist and Nobel laureate Sheldon Glashow once supposedly described string theory",
                "as the theory of everything",
                "that predicts nothing."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 9450,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "At the end of the day,",
                "if string theory does not provide us",
                "with a testable prediction&mdash;whether it be in the context",
                "of elementary particle physics or cosmology and black hole physics&mdash;then nobody",
                "should believe it."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 100,
            "typeflat": "p",
            "contentflat": [
                ""
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 5700,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "The power of science is an acceptance and openness to the notion",
                "that we are fallible and must therefore be corrected",
                "by nature herself."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 3900,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "Many other human belief systems start off",
                "with the assumption that the answer is already known."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 3600,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "In science, it's precisely the opposite; we start",
                "out admitting to not knowing the answer."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 10950,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "So as we struggle with our marriages",
                "of space and time, our addition",
                "of extra dimensions, our paradigm shifts",
                "from little billiard balls to little pieces",
                "of spaghetti, these exercises are all subjected",
                "to a single question: Is it there in the laboratory?"
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 1050,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "Can you find its evidence?"
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 3750,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "Until that happens, I am of the opinion that you",
                "should be skeptical about string theory."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 100,
            "typeflat": "p",
            "contentflat": [
                ""
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 9600,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "On the other hand, there is a kind of elegance",
                "to string theory, and given the history",
                "of how theoretical physics has evolved thus far,",
                "it is totally conceivable that some if not all",
                "of these ideas will turn out to be correct."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 100,
            "typeflat": "p",
            "contentflat": [
                ""
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 3900,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "NOVA: Is there any conceivable way, then, to look",
                "for evidence that string theory is correct?"
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 100,
            "typeflat": "p",
            "contentflat": [
                ""
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 5700,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "Gates: All of this activity in",
                "which we engage will be for naught unless",
                "at some point there is experimental verification of these ideas."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 3750,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "Interestingly enough, we have some tantalizing hints already",
                "that this may be occurring."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 3450,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "Evidence for superpartners may have begun",
                "to emerge in the laboratory."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 6900,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "Superpartners come from supersymmetry,",
                "and supersymmetry is part of superstrings,",
                "so we may be on the cusp of beginning",
                "to see experimental verification."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 3150,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "[For more on experimental support",
                "for supersymmetry, see Smashing Pictures.]"
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 100,
            "typeflat": "p",
            "contentflat": [
                ""
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 1350,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "NOVA: What is supersymmetry?"
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 100,
            "typeflat": "p",
            "contentflat": [
                ""
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 4500,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "Gates: In our world as we observe it",
                "in the laboratory, the universe breaks into,",
                "roughly speaking, two pieces."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 3600,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "One of these pieces is matter, such",
                "as electrons, quarks, protons,",
                "neutrons&mdash;what things are made of."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 5550,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "The other half of our universe are the things",
                "that cause the matter to clump together&mdash;the forces",
                "of nature&mdash;and each force has carriers."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 6900,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "The carrier of the gravitational force is the graviton;",
                "the carrier",
                "of the electromagnetic force is the photon; the carrier",
                "of the strong force are things called gluons."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 1800,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "Well, gee, what kind of unification is that?"
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 2100,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "The answer is, it's no unification at all."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 100,
            "typeflat": "p",
            "contentflat": [
                ""
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 1350,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "So let's try one more marriage."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 4800,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "Let's look for a marriage where the stuff",
                "of our universe and the things that cause the stuff",
                "to clump together are intertwined."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 4350,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "We know this occurs in string theory, but it also occurs",
                "in a smaller theory called supersymmetry."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 4500,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "That's the first place we saw this marriage occur,",
                "and that's in fact what brought me",
                "into theoretical physics."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 5700,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "In a supersymmetrical theory, there are new forms",
                "of matter and energy called \"superpartners\"",
                "that are required for this unification."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 100,
            "typeflat": "p",
            "contentflat": [
                ""
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 2850,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "NOVA: What will evidence",
                "for supersymmetry mean for string theory?"
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 100,
            "typeflat": "p",
            "contentflat": [
                ""
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 3600,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "Gates: Supersymmetry will be one of the signposts pointing",
                "to the correctness of superstrings."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 2850,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "Superstrings are in some sense very far removed",
                "from our reality."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 2850,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "When you take most superstring theories",
                "apart they contain superpartners."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 8700,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "So if a laboratory experiment such as the one being conducted",
                "at Brookhaven reveals the presence of superpartners,",
                "that will point to the increased possibility",
                "that superstring theory is correct."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 100,
            "typeflat": "p",
            "contentflat": [
                ""
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 6000,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "<br />Slow to take hold <br />NOVA:",
                "String theory was introduced in the '60s,",
                "and it is only in the last decade or two",
                "that it has become widely studied."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 1500,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "Why was string theory ignored at first?"
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 100,
            "typeflat": "p",
            "contentflat": [
                ""
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 1200,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "Gates: For a number of reasons."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 4800,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "Theoretical physics is of course done",
                "by humans, which means that there is a culture,",
                "a societal norm, among physicists."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 4800,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "That societal norm has a lot",
                "of inertia&mdash;it's very difficult",
                "to change the opinion of that community."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 4050,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "And so unless very strong evidence is presented,",
                "the community tends not to want to change ideas."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 2400,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "That is true for physicists just",
                "as it is for other people."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 9300,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "So when this radical notion",
                "that there were more dimensions",
                "than we have traditionally accepted came into physics",
                "with essentially no experimental support,",
                "the built-in conservatism of the community took over."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 100,
            "typeflat": "p",
            "contentflat": [
                ""
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 3300,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "<br />&ldquo;There&rsquo;s a saying",
                "that old physicists accept new ideas when they die.&rdquo;"
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 100,
            "typeflat": "p",
            "contentflat": [
                ""
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 1000,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "&nbsp;"
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 100,
            "typeflat": "p",
            "contentflat": [
                ""
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 2700,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "There's a saying",
                "that old physicists accept new ideas when they die."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 2700,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "It's the next generation",
                "that brings new ideas to their full fruition."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 4800,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "When you get to be an old physicist like me,",
                "you know a lot of stuff, and it acts",
                "like a ballast on a ship; it pulls you down."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 1950,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "You have all the weight",
                "of these other things that you know."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 6750,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "And sometimes an idea,",
                "like a small fairy or a sprite, passes",
                "by and you say, \"Ah, I don't know what that is,",
                "but it can't be very important.\" Well, sometimes it is."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 100,
            "typeflat": "p",
            "contentflat": [
                ""
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 2100,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "NOVA: What will it mean",
                "if string theory is correct?"
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 100,
            "typeflat": "p",
            "contentflat": [
                ""
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 10500,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "Gates: In a general sense it means that a generation",
                "of physicists will possess a set of tools and some images",
                "about the universe that will allow them",
                "to probe the universe and understand the laws",
                "of the universe well beyond what we can do today."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 100,
            "typeflat": "p",
            "contentflat": [
                ""
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 4800,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "Answering the question of what the practical benefits",
                "of that understanding will be is",
                "beyond my capabilities."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 2250,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "But I can look backward",
                "to 1864 and Maxwell and his equations."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 4050,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "And one can imagine saying, \"Professor Maxwell,",
                "what do your equations mean?\" He",
                "would struggle for answers."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 4650,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "He would say, \"Well, you know,",
                "the electric and magnetic phenomena are not separate,",
                "they're part of a unity."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 7800,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "They make a prediction that waves",
                "of electromagnetic energy travel in space and time",
                "with the velocity of light.\" But beyond that I think he",
                "would be rather hard-pressed to tell you what it means."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 3150,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "One hundred and fifty years later we",
                "can answer this question very easily."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 2700,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "A large fraction",
                "of our technological basis rests on his work."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 100,
            "typeflat": "p",
            "contentflat": [
                ""
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 1950,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "So if string theory is correct, what does it mean?"
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 4350,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "Well, one can imagine 150 or 200 years",
                "from now some marvelous piece",
                "of technology that's beyond my imagining."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 6900,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "Maybe it's a transporter",
                "from \"Star Trek,\" perhaps it's warp drive,",
                "maybe our species finally is released from this prison",
                "of being contained in a single solar system."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 100,
            "typeflat": "p",
            "contentflat": [
                ""
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 4650,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "NOVA: Aside from possible technologies 200 years",
                "from now, how else is your work meaningful",
                "to the general public?"
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 100,
            "typeflat": "p",
            "contentflat": [
                ""
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 7200,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "Gates: The kind of physics",
                "that my community engages in&mdash;trying",
                "to understand the most fundamental structure and issues",
                "for our<br />universe&mdash;is a birthright for all of us."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 3000,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "For me there is a personal joy",
                "in participating in that adventure."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 3750,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "It belongs to everybody, just",
                "like great art and great music belongs to everybody."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 1500,
            "typeflat": "sentence",
            "contentflat": [
                "Great science belongs to everybody."
            ]
        },
        {
            "timeflat": 2000,
